Commentary Text: Shami to Rossouw, out Caught by Saha!! Absolute corker. Test match bowling, Test match like pokey defence and classic Test match outside edge. There's nothing T20 about this delivery, all thanks to Mohammed Shami's art of swing bowling. Gets this to land on a good length and extracts late away movement in the corridor of uncertainty. Rossouw feels for it and has a poke after covering his off-stump, thick outside edge and Saha completes the formalities. DC three down inside three overs. Rossouw c Saha b Shami 8(6) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Priyam Garg, no ball, out Warner Run Out!! It's getting bad to worse for DC. Priyam Garg showed a bit of intent to take a single the previous delivery but didn't get the desired response from his partner and this time he flicks it straight to Rashid to short mid-wicket. Called for a quick single and didn't move. Warner had committed and never stopped. Kept running to the striker's end and by the time he saw his partner, he was left stranded in the middle of the pitch. Rashid smartly decides against the throw and runs towards the stumps to effect the easiest of run-outs. Amidst all the drama, it has been deemed a front foot no ball... Warner run out (Rashid Khan) 2(2)

Commentary Text: Nortje to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Manish Pandey!! Shubman Gill falls cheaply! The DC players are cock-a-hoop as Nortje strikes off his first ball. He pitches it up and bowls it well outside off, Shubman Gill gets drawn into it and plays a drive away from his body. Only manages to hit it straight towards cover-point and Manish Pandey makes no mistake. It's a weak area for Shubman Gill, he also got out to Starc a few times in this manner in India's last ODI series against Australia. Shubman Gill c Manish Pandey b Nortje 6(7) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, out Caught by Philip Salt!! Saha was looking all at sea against Khaleel Ahmed and he eventually departs! He flirted with danger in the third ball of the over but survived. But, this time he is not lucky. Pitched up ball well outside off, Saha goes for a loose drive away from his body and only manages to edge it behind. Salt dives to his right and takes a good catch. Sunil Gavaskar on air mentions that he is practicing the straight drive while walking off. Too late for that. Saha c Philip Salt b Khaleel Ahmed 0(6)
